# Scope And Phase

- RULE: Follow the current ordered slices: community surfaces, web planner shell, browser-local planner state, then the external AI connection flow.
- RULE: Implement `apps/api`, `apps/web`, onboarding, planner-local state, and student-code foundations before freezing the final AI route contract.
- RULE: Keep accessibility review and WCAG-aligned product hardening inside the active web-runtime scope even before a formal conformance claim exists.
- RULE: Keep the current active slice broad enough to include official browser bootstrap data, planner settings, local search, inscriptions guidance, project/editorial surfaces, traceable news links, and SEO hardening.
- RULE: Keep authenticated scraping and parser self-repair out of the current runtime slice unless doctrine changes first.
- RULE: Keep detailed campus mapping out of the current runtime slice except for clearly marked placeholder surfaces.
